The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during his visit to the U.S. Virgin Islands in the aftermath of Hurricane Maria. Pence expressed support and solidarity with the people of the U.S. Virgin Islands, promising assistance and resources to help the territory recover. He commended the efforts of the military, including the Virgin Islands National Guard and National Guard units from other states, and thanked FEMA for their work on the ground. Pence also acknowledged the presence of various government officials and expressed gratitude for their leadership. He highlighted the resilience and determination of the people of the U.S. Virgin Islands and praised their can-do attitude. The Vice President concluded his remarks by assuring the governor and the people that the U.S. government is committed to providing long-term support for the recovery efforts.